sect1.para:
if you want to add a sumti to a place other than x2, you can use a FA tag. So:
la renas. klama fi la melbn. Rena is going from Melbourne le klama be fi la melbn. The one going from Melbourne
ti xatra fo lei dinske This is a letter about economics le xatra be fo lei dinske The letter about economics

In this lesson, we have covered the following:
Internal sumti (be, bei, be'o);
Internal sumti attached with sumti tcita (pe, fi'e);
Restrictive relative clauses (poi, ku'o, ke'a)
Non-restrictive relative clauses (noi, no, no'e, ne)
